params._result: the games either to be created or resolved.

requestSchedule(bytes32,uint256,uint256,.details: Requests the 'schedule' endpoint. Result is an array of GameCreate or GameResolve encoded (see structs).

params._date: the starting time of the event as a UNIX timestamp in seconds.
params._market: the number associated with the type of market (see Data Conversions).
params._payment: the LINK amount in Juels (i.e. 10^18 aka 1 LINK).

requestSchedule(bytes32,uint256,uint256,.details: Requests the 'schedule' endpoint. Result is an array of GameCreate or GameResolve encoded (see structs).

params._date: the date to request events by, as a UNIX timestamp in seconds.
params._gameIds: the list of game IDs to filter by for market `1`, otherwise the value is ignored.
params._market: the context of the games data to be requested: `0` (markets to be created), `1` (markets to be resolved).
params._payment: the LINK amount in Juels (i.e. 10^18 aka 1 LINK).
